#: 21337012-0-1488
msgctxt "21337012-0-1488"
msgid ""
"A Nord blacksmith feels a particular affinity with his anvil, bellows, "
"hammer, and tongs. For the Nord, the creation of fine (if inelegant) weapons "
"and armor is as important as proficiency with a blade, axe, or hammer. Such "
"skills are learned from youth and are almost mandatory. As the Nord armorer "
"and weaponsmith perfect their techniques, the forge becomes a second home. "
"Close by is the tanning rack, where the hides of every beast of the north "
"have been measured for their levels of durability and flexibility. Layered "
"on top is iron, steel, and corundum alloys. The result is a steel that holds "
"tighter and bites sharper than weapons from other realms. \n"
"\n"
"When Nords refer to their blades as \"\"stinging,\"\" they mean more than "
"its cutting power: superstitious Nord smiths are said to add a drop of wild "
"bee honey into everything they create. The whys and wherefores are misplaced "
"in long-forgotten lore, but the practice is widespread. To this day, no Nord "
"armorer would work a forge without first crumbling honeycomb into his "
"quenching tub."
msgstr ""

